Dialogue: 0,0:00:44.70,0:00:47.47,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,A dream... Right?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.15,0:02:23.51,Title,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(281,534)}#08 Winter Days, Where the Heart Is
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.32,0:02:50.07,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Were you holding back today?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.07,0:02:51.20,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.87,0:02:56.08,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You didn't seem as hard on me\Nas you did yesterday.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.08,0:02:58.93,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Because your abilities have improved.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.87,0:03:00.74,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,They have?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.25,0:03:04.66,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Specifically, your stance no longer \Nhas any wasted movement.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.05,0:03:06.55,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.80,0:03:09.25,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I was only mimicking his moves...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.80,0:03:15.05,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So you are using Archer's technique, \Nnot mine, as the basis for your study.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.77,0:03:18.64,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You can tell that?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.64,0:03:19.94,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.94,0:03:24.02,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,After all, you had no fundamental stance at the start.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.02,0:03:27.10,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry... I didn't mean it as \Na slight against you, Saber.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.07,0:03:32.65,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I guess he was in my head because \NI was around him all day yesterday.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.78,0:03:35.73,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,There is no need to apologize.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.54,0:03:42.63,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If Archer's style is a better fit for \Nyou, it isn't my place to judge.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.63,0:03:43.74,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Um, Saber...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.66,0:04:15.87,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Good morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.91,0:04:19.50,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, how rare to see you late.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.50,0:04:22.11,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Fujimura-sensei was quite furious.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.21,0:04:26.20,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Finally gracing us with your presence?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.21,0:04:30.29,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Shinji...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.51,0:04:33.79,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You let it go to your head, and now \Nyou think you're hot stuff?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.34,0:04:36.54,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Still, I'm glad you came.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.31,0:04:41.30,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If you weren't here, it wouldn't be any fun.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.04,0:05:05.54,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What's up? Not going to the cafeteria?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.54,0:05:09.85,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I should like nothing better, but... \NWell, just have a look at that.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.97,0:05:16.51,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,There can be no doubt.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.51,0:05:21.31,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That girl is peeking into our classroom, \Nnonchalant, yet brazen as can be.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.31,0:05:25.85,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It is not "The one you wait for will not come," \Nbut "The one you wait for will not notice."
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.85,0:05:31.48,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,She looks about to snap, like one who \Nhad left a birthday gift for someone,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.48,0:05:34.85,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,but even after a year, the recipient failed to notice.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.22,0:05:56.55,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Where are you going, Tohsaka?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.55,0:06:00.26,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It's lunchtime, so obviously, \NI'm going to eat lunch.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.26,0:06:01.43,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, right.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.68,0:06:03.88,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Well, find a nice spot.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.02,0:06:06.22,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'm eating in the student council office.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.44,0:06:08.40,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Wait just a minute!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.40,0:06:11.86,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What, did you forget your \Nlunch money or something?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.86,0:06:14.33,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I can share my lunch with you if—
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.67,0:06:16.27,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Of course I didn't, you numbskull!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.96,0:06:28.26,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Over there, you'll be sitting in the wind.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.02,0:06:53.91,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.11,0:06:58.18,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,About yesterday, I mean.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.70,0:07:01.66,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I've used a Command Seal on Archer.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.66,0:07:06.13,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I ordered him not to attack you, \Nas long as our alliance stands.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.46,0:07:11.45,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I know it doesn't make up for \Nanything, but I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.75,0:07:16.20,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That isn't something you should be apologizing for.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.26,0:07:22.44,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I gave him free rein yesterday, so I'm responsible.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.93,0:07:24.31,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.31,0:07:27.60,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If that's what you say, I'll go along with it.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.60,0:07:32.09,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Besides, I was partly to blame, \Nand if he hadn't been there, I...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.11,0:07:36.18,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Let's call it even.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.69,0:07:39.02,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.11,0:07:42.74,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So where is Archer today?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.99,0:07:44.78,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I left him at home.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.78,0:07:46.10,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Oh.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.83,0:07:51.04,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Crap, lunch break is over!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.79,0:07:55.60,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Hang out with me for a bit.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.55,0:07:59.86,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Skipping a class every once in a while\Nwon't do any harm, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.81,0:08:13.59,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Why are you so fixated on strengthening magic?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.48,0:08:18.60,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I've tried different kinds, \Nbut that's the only one I can do.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.28,0:08:23.99,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I can store up simple power, alter its flow,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.99,0:08:27.67,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,and convert and store mana in various objects.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.67,0:08:29.19,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Should you be telling me this?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.79,0:08:32.86,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You told me yours, so it wouldn't be fair if I didn't.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.29,0:08:40.47,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I showed you earlier, but this is my Magic Crest.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.47,0:08:43.54,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,In the Tohsaka family, we pass \Ndown conversion techniques.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.14,0:08:49.37,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Our specialty is the transfer of power, \Neither in ourselves or in others.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.94,0:08:57.80,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Did you know that the Matous are a mage family?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.40,0:08:59.48,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.48,0:09:03.56,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But Father told me that they're no longer \Nconsidered a bloodline of mages.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.28,0:09:06.45,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Wait a second!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.45,0:09:08.52,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You knew that Shinji was a Master?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.12,0:09:15.03,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry... I just found out this morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.58,0:09:19.03,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'd written him off as someone who \Ncouldn't possibly be a Master.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.55,0:09:22.09,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What are you going to do about him?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.09,0:09:24.05,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Attack him right away?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.30,0:09:28.46,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I wouldn't attack someone haphazardly \Njust because he's a Master.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.72,0:09:30.71,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Actually, you did... You attacked me.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.02,0:09:34.48,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I only did because you weren't taking this seriously.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.48,0:09:36.18,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It was an exceptional exception!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.31,0:09:41.65,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Anyway, our enemy is the Master \Nwho's hiding at the school.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.65,0:09:43.77,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,For now, let's focus on them.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.74,0:09:49.74,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Then you're saying there \Nare four here, at school?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.74,0:09:51.19,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Wouldn't there have to be?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.75,0:09:54.96,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,As a Master, Shinji has no power.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.21,0:09:58.92,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I told him I'd turn a blind eye if he behaved himself,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.92,0:10:00.88,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,so I don't expect any trouble from him.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.88,0:10:02.63,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Wait, Tohsaka...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.63,0:10:05.20,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Tell me more about that.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.80,0:10:08.68,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Shinji was the one who approached me.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.68,0:10:12.97,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,He said, "Since we're both Masters, \Nshall we join forces?"
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.97,0:10:16.22,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Naturally, I turned him down, but he \Nwouldn't take no for an answer.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.85,0:10:22.82,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So finally, I said, "I already have \NEmiya-kun, so I don't need you."
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.02,0:10:25.04,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Right to his face!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.53,0:10:29.23,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So that's why he was acting strangely...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.16,0:10:32.36,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Well, what's the plan, Tohsaka?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.00,0:10:39.20,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Shinji might not be a mage, \Nbut he did put up that field.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.71,0:10:45.13,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You didn't notice that?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.88,0:10:46.93,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, no.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.18,0:10:49.43,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If we aren't careful, Shinji might...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.16,0:11:11.62,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That's great!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.62,0:11:14.74,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,This is how Servants ought to be!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.35,0:11:42.01,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What's going on?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.19,0:11:45.61,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Keep generating mana within your body, Emiya-kun.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.69,0:11:47.94,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Sakura!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.94,0:12:07.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wai—
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.19,0:12:26.48,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,She's breathing.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.48,0:12:28.61,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It isn't too late to save them.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.61,0:12:31.43,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,We have to find Shinji and take down this field.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.41,0:12:42.61,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Emiya-kun!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.60,0:13:04.06,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What are these things?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.06,0:13:05.11,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Golems.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.11,0:13:06.64,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,A type of familiar!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.24,0:13:11.86,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'll summon Saber.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.24,0:13:15.73,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You used a Command Seal yesterday, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.70,0:13:19.04,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That means it's my turn.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.29,0:13:21.40,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Emiya-kun...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.55,0:13:32.41,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Please...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.80,0:13:34.05,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Come to me,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.05,0:13:35.80,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Saber!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.78,0:13:59.73,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Saber!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.91,0:14:02.29,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I have come in response to your summons.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.29,0:14:03.61,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Master, the situation?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.04,0:14:05.37,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It's as you can see.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.37,0:14:07.58,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,A Servant has set up a Bounded Field.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.58,0:14:09.54,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I want to dismantle it as quickly as possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.54,0:14:10.95,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Archer, do you hear me?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.55,0:14:15.47,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I sense the presence of a Servant on this floor.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.47,0:14:16.87,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,No way! Here?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.87,0:14:17.46,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Rin?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.55,0:14:21.79,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,No, if that's what you sense, I'm sure you're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.14,0:14:25.10,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But I sense the field's \Npoint of origin on the first floor.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.10,0:14:29.80,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The Servant's on this floor, even though \Nthe field is coming from the first?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.15,0:14:33.72,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I can't say for sure, but that's what I sense.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.03,0:14:36.57,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Rin, where is Archer?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.57,0:14:39.48,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If he's here, he can give a better assessment.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.48,0:14:42.41,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'm calling him, but he isn't answering!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.41,0:14:45.79,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,This Bounded Field cuts us \Noff from the outside world.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.79,0:14:48.35,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,A Command Seal is the only form \Nof contact that can get through.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.25,0:14:53.20,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,We should consider this a field designed \Nto separate Master from Servant.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.17,0:14:57.04,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The enemy is planning to settle things here, Shirou.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.64,0:15:03.64,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Saber, there's a Servant on this floor, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.68,0:15:06.43,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You handle that one.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.69,0:15:08.55,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,We're going to destroy the Bounded Field.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.81,0:15:10.09,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Emiya-kun?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.31,0:15:12.89,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It's dangerous, but that is the correct decision.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.69,0:15:16.47,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Now, while I keep them busy.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.82,0:15:18.15,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.15,0:15:19.38,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Let's go, Tohsaka.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.20,0:15:22.06,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Damn it!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.20,0:15:32.04,Next,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Chemistry Room
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.17,0:15:34.05,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Very good.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.05,0:15:37.84,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,This is how a first-rate Master does things.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.84,0:15:42.00,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Once this is over, maybe I'll go check \Nout Emiya's withered husk.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.64,0:15:51.18,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What is it, Rider?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.86,0:15:57.07,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, what's the deal?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.32,0:15:59.03,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,How are you able to move?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.28,0:16:04.49,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Stay away, damn it...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.49,0:16:06.90,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'm warning you, you'd better stay away!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.04,0:16:09.54,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What the hell?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.71,0:16:13.67,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Rider!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.70,0:16:45.23,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Rider-class Servant...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.06,0:17:14.76,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Caster...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.69,0:17:19.73,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Tohsaka, did you locate the field's point of origin?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.73,0:17:21.14,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, it's right over there.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.14,0:17:23.06,Next,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Chemistry Room
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.32,0:17:23.03,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That room up ahead!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.20,0:17:25.61,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Damn, they're persistent!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.20,0:17:29.44,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Are we ever gonna run out of these guys?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.83,0:17:31.50,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Shirou, stand back.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.96,0:17:35.32,Default - italics,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Ein Körper
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.54,0:17:36.74,Default - italics,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,ist ein
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.00,0:17:38.87,Default - italics,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Körper!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.35,0:17:55.56,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Shinji...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.57,0:18:04.45,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Don't give me any of your excuses.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.45,0:18:08.45,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'll make you pay for what \Nyou've done, no matter what!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.45,0:18:11.20,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Y-You've got it wrong! \NWrong! Wrong!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.20,0:18:13.69,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It wasn't me... It wasn't me! It wasn't me!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.25,0:18:16.00,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It wasn't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.00,0:18:18.67,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Take this field down right now!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.67,0:18:21.71,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If you say no, I'll blow your \Nsniveling face clean off!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.71,0:18:25.58,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'm telling you, you've got it wrong! \NIt wasn't me! She was killed by—
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.68,0:18:26.61,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Shinji!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.98,0:18:34.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ouch, ouch...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.14,0:18:34.96,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Tohsaka!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.10,0:18:39.84,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Tohsaka, over there.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.58,0:18:56.33,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,She's dead.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.89,0:19:15.05,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Looks like you survived by allowing \Nyour Servant to be killed.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.73,0:19:19.02,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But if you saw the killer's face, \Nit'll be your turn next.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.02,0:19:21.61,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Th-That won't happen!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.61,0:19:24.15,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I don't have a Servant!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.15,0:19:25.78,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not a Master anymore...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.78,0:19:28.66,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You two are the ones who still \Nhave targets on your backs!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.66,0:19:29.85,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That's true.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.20,0:19:33.95,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Even if you still have Command Seals, \Nyou're no threat.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.95,0:19:35.94,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Gnats can't kill anyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.94,0:19:37.75,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,G-Gnats?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.75,0:19:39.21,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You're calling me a gnat?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.21,0:19:42.72,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Be glad I'm not comparing you to a harmful bug!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.42,0:19:46.08,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If you saw who did it, answer me.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.38,0:19:49.56,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Right now, that's your only value to us.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.47,0:19:52.43,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Talk!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.43,0:19:55.50,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What kind of Servant was it that took out yours?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.64,0:19:58.13,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,H-How should I know, moron?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.13,0:20:01.68,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Y-You're the ones who should be scared...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.15,0:20:06.85,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Because you're the ones it'll come after next!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.12,0:20:17.95,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It's okay, Tohsaka.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.95,0:20:20.17,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,They're all still breathing.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.17,0:20:21.20,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,They're breathing?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.58,0:20:24.03,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, they're alive.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.38,0:20:27.01,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,All we have to do is call for help.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.71,0:20:30.87,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,With something like this, do they need \Nan ambulance? Or should we call...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.51,0:20:34.18,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,We should call the church.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.18,0:20:37.21,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If we explain the situation to Kirei, \Nhe'll see to everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.72,0:20:38.89,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.14,0:20:41.01,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'll call him right away, then.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.78,0:20:48.82,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You were fighting Caster?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.82,0:20:53.64,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, although it was merely Caster's \Nshadow that controlled the familiars.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.99,0:20:58.83,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I see. Then the real Caster \Nhasn't left Ryuudou Temple.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.83,0:21:03.03,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Knowing her, she might have manipulated \NShinji, to lure Rider into a trap.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.00,0:21:07.16,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Then Rider was killed through deception?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.59,0:21:08.71,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Crap.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.71,0:21:13.48,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Still, we know that Caster's Master \Nis someone at this school.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.48,0:21:14.29,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Right...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.87,0:21:18.63,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Tohsaka, if you have something to say, say it.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.64,0:21:22.27,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Emiya-kun, you're really level-headed.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.52,0:21:23.88,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I was surprised.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.48,0:21:26.36,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I wasn't calm.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.36,0:21:28.39,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I was probably so pissed, I lost control.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.82,0:21:32.27,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Even so, you knew the extent of everyone's injuries.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.49,0:21:35.85,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I couldn't manage that.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.70,0:21:38.69,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It wasn't a big deal.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.45,0:21:41.69,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'm used to seeing dead bodies.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.87,0:21:45.63,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Used to it?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:26.06,0:23:29.19,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'll find out whether or not he's a Master.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:29.19,0:23:32.94,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Anyone who isn't up for this \Nbattle should just leave.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:32.94,0:23:34.86,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And you call yourself a hero?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:34.86,0:23:38.99,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Then you're saying that you \Nare prepared to fight?
